wiki.summary: "thank u, next" is about moving on from past relationships and being content and grateful for the lessons learned. She expresses gratitude for the self-growth she experienced from each relationship. The lyrics show appreciation for being able to move on positively, with a newfound strength that came from her mistakes, pains and lessons. The song is a reminder to never be ashamed of having once loved, and that even after heartbreak and struggles, life goes on and is better. Read more on Last.fm.

The lyrics show appreciation for being able to move on positively, with a newfound strength that came from her mistakes, pains and lessons. The song is a reminder to never be ashamed of having once loved, and that even after heartbreak and struggles, life goes on and is better. On the song, Grande mentioned four of her exes: Big Sean, Ricky Alvarez, Pete Davidson and Mac Miller. Read more on Last.fm.
